This paper is about developing an end-to-end neural model for dialogue systems that can select appropriate knowledge to generate informative responses. The paper focuses on natural language processing and machine learning techniques, which are typically covered in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of neural networks and deep learning, which are relevant to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper proposes a novel knowledge selection mechanism that involves both prior and posterior distributions, which is related to probabilistic modeling and Bayesian inference, which are covered in the cs.LG (Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques for selecting appropriate knowledge, which is relevant to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category.
